It was my first time experience here. I ordered chai tea and it was great. Then I ordered tom yam goong. The flavor of fish sauce was quite strong. I tasted salty overcome the tamarind.  I ordered curry and that one the decent one for my taste. Little bit spicy which is I like. The decor was nice, I felt comfortable. The service was fast and great waiter. There is a board sign for cellphone user ..lol... They have Indonesian coffee which I should try next time.  The private parking lot was in the back of the building. I might go back to try something else next time.
